Response to
Episode 1 - "Standing Up in the Milky Way"
@-------------------------------------------------
-One thing that amazed me is how BIG everything is. Especially Jupitar--scary yet magical.
-How can we tell the difference between light from stars in the Milky Way and light from other galaxies?
-Why am I focusing so much on college if I matter so little...
-Lift the curtain, the boundary of the known world, and explore beyond. This philosophy can be applied to other sciences, not just astromony. Some may ask if the pursuit of knowledge, if science, is worth our time, money, tax dollars. These people should watch this show, a VERY pusuasive argument for science is layed out. 
-I like how the entire show emphasized that our knowledge today will certainly be enhanced in the future. For example, Tyson said that the Big Bang is as far back as we can see, for now. 
-It is staggering to think about the randomness involved in our (human) history. Although the more I think about it, the chances increase because of the gazillions of planets, all of which have a chance (allbeit low) of containing life.
